article.description: LaMarcus Reed had 16 points and eight rebounds to lead Texas-Arlington to a 62-52 victory over Stephen F. Austin on Saturday night.
article.headline: Texas-Arlington puts away Stephen F. Austin
article.linkText: Texas-Arlington puts away Stephen F. Austin
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- LaMarcus Reed had 16 points and eight rebounds to lead Texas-Arlington to a 62-52 victory over Stephen F. Austin on Saturday night. Bo Ingram added 14 points for the Mavericks (9-9, 3-2 Southland Conference). Dion Prewster had 10 points and 11 rebounds for the Lumberjacks (11-5, 2-2). Texas-Arlington led 30-25 at intermission and maintained its cushion throughout the second half. Reed and Darius Richardson hit 3-pointers to help give the Mavericks a 50-38 lead with 6:53 remaining, and Stephen F. Austin got no closer than seven the rest of the way.
